\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 2. F. sancta} (Janka) Melderis, {\i op. cit.} 319 (1978) ({\i Festuca sancta} Janka, {\i Brachypodium sanctum} (Janka) Janka, {\i Agropyron sanctum }(Janka) Hackel). Stems 45-110 cm. Leaves 7-30 cm × 2-3 mm usually inrolled, minutely scabridulous on the inside, smooth and glabrous on the outside; leaf-sheaths disintegrating into a mass of reticulate fibres. Spikes 7-9 cm, with 5-8 spikelets. Spikelets 1-1·2(-1·5) cm, green. Glumes lanceolate, usually with an awn up to 1·5 mm, the lower 6-7 mm, 1- to 3-veined, the upper 8-9 mm, 3- to 5-veined. Lemmas 9-10 mm, 5-veined, with an awn 4·5-9 mm. Palea nearly as long as or slightly longer than the lemma. Anthers 4 mm.{\i  Calcareous rocks. • Mountains of N. Greece and S.W. Bulgaria.} Bu Gr.
